# ↓↓↓ Your Environment Variables ↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓
# Place your environment variables in this section!


# ─── Plate Selection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Active database plate: sqlite | postgres | supabase | mongo
HACKPLATE_DB=sqlite
# Active auth plate: local | auth0 | keycloak
HACKPLATE_AUTH=local

# ─── App Workers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Number of Uvicorn workers to run the API while started in production mode.
HACKPLATE_WORKERS=4

# ─── Secret Key ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by all auth plates for JWT signing, password reset, and verification tokens.
# Generate with: hackplate regenkey  (auto-set by hackplate init)
SECRET_KEY=

# ─── CORS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated list of allowed origins. Defaults to Vite dev server.
CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173
CORS_ALLOW_CREDENTIALS=true
CORS_ALLOW_METHODS=*
CORS_ALLOW_HEADERS=*

# ─── SQLite (HACKPLATE_DB=sqlite) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the SQLite database file, relative to project root.
SQLITE_DB_PATH=db.sqlite3

# ─── Postgres (HACKPLATE_DB=postgres) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Provide either POSTGRES_URL or the individual connection fields below.
POSTGRES_URL=
POSTGRES_NAME=
POSTGRES_USERNAME=
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=
POSTGRES_HOST=localhost
POSTGRES_PORT=5432
POSTGRES_SSL_REQUIRED=false

# ─── Supabase (HACKPLATE_DB=supabase) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase is managed Postgres — uses the same POSTGRES_* variables above.
# SSL is required by default; set POSTGRES_SSL_REQUIRED=false to override.
# (No additional variables needed — configure the POSTGRES_* section above.)

# ─── MongoDB (HACKPLATE_DB=mongo) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Provide either MONGO_URL or the individual connection fields below.
# MONGO_USERNAME and MONGO_PASSWORD are optional for unauthenticated local instances.
MONGO_URL=
MONGO_NAME=hackplate
MONGO_USERNAME=
MONGO_PASSWORD=
MONGO_HOST=localhost
MONGO_PORT=27017
MONGO_SSL_REQUIRED=false

# ─── Auth0 (HACKPLATE_AUTH=auth0) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTH0_DOMAIN: your tenant domain, e.g. dev-xxxx.us.auth0.com
# AUTH0_AUDIENCE: API identifier configured in the Auth0 dashboard
# AUTH0_M2M_*: machine-to-machine app credentials for server-side API calls
AUTH0_DOMAIN=
AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=
AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET=
AUTH0_AUDIENCE=
AUTH0_M2M_CLIENT_ID=
AUTH0_M2M_CLIENT_SECRET=
AUTH0_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8000/docs
AUTH0_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:8000/auth/callback
AUTH0_SECURE_COOKIES=false

# ─── Keycloak (HACKPLATE_AUTH=keycloak) ───────────────────────────────────────
# KEYCLOAK_USE_LOCAL: bool toggle to choose between external or docker service
# KEYCLOAK_HOST: internal URL used by the app container (docker service name).
# KEYCLOAK_EXTERNAL_URL: browser-facing URL used for redirects and kcsync.
# KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_SECRET: auto-populated by `hackplate kcsync`.
KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin
KEYCLOAK_USE_LOCAL=true
KEYCLOAK_REALM=hackplate
KEYCLOAK_HOST=http://keycloak:8080
KEYCLOAK_EXTERNAL_URL=http://localhost:8080
KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_ID=hackplate
KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_SECRET=
KEYCLOAK_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:8000/auth/callback
KEYCLOAK_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8000/docs
KEYCLOAK_SECURE_COOKIES=false
